The paper deals with the Delaunay triangulation of moving points, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing the topological changes in the Delaunay triangulation, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves obtaining upper bounds, which could place it under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
